race.comment: WEAPONS HOT (1) showed good early speed and led into the straight before fading to finish fourth, beaten 2.25L, over 1103m at Geraldton. This looks a much better assignment for him and he was dominant in tougher company two back at Moora. Looks the one to beat. WINNING ACES (4) resumes today without a trial but looks well placed back in grade. Catarino's 2kg claim comes in handy and if he can hold a position from a favourable barrier, he'll make his presence felt. THE CHIEF JUSTICE (3) faded badly first-up at York when sitting on the speed over 1300m. It was a disappointing effort on the back of an impressive trial coming in. Blinkers go back on now and sharp improvement is on the cards. SOLAR SYSTEM (2) turned in a better performance last start at York when a $6 chance and now gets Gray replacing the apprentice. Not out of this. PERCUSSION PRINCE (6) is next best.
